1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,208
Day 9.

2
00:00:01,208 --> 00:00:03,944
For the first time, I didn't watch the charts.

3
00:00:03,944 --> 00:00:06,250
The bot made three trades.

4
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:07,777
I checked once.

5
00:00:07,777 --> 00:00:09,277
I can't code.

6
00:00:09,277 --> 00:00:11,555
9 years in crypto.

7
00:00:11,555 --> 00:00:13,763
AI trades my thousand.

8
00:00:13,763 --> 00:00:14,833
Day 9.

9
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:17,652
That day I spent rewriting the website.

10
00:00:17,652 --> 00:00:22,234
Reframed every line from trading product to social experiment.

11
00:00:22,234 --> 00:00:25,930
Meanwhile, the bot made three trades on its own.

12
00:00:25,930 --> 00:00:28,222
Net down about a dollar eighty.

13
00:00:28,222 --> 00:00:29,763
I looked once.

14
00:00:29,763 --> 00:00:31,375
Then closed the tab.

15
00:00:31,375 --> 00:00:33,847
Not because I didn't care.

16
00:00:33,847 --> 00:00:37,388
Because I'd finally built something I could stop policing.

17
00:00:37,388 --> 00:00:41,930
The real test of any system you build is — can you stop watching it?

18
00:00:41,930 --> 00:00:44,722
If you can't, you didn't build a system.

19
00:00:44,722 --> 00:00:46,569
You built a second job.

20
00:00:46,569 --> 00:00:49,013
Most people can't tell the difference.

21
00:00:49,013 --> 00:00:53,277
That was the first day I rented my attention back from the bot.

22
00:00:53,277 --> 00:00:55,611
It was cheaper than I expected.

23
00:00:55,611 --> 00:00:59,791
Day 10 tomorrow — Twitter took my account without warning.

24
00:00:59,791 --> 00:01:01,194
Follow along.

